This project uses the Geonames API (http://www.geonames.org) to obtain the location of a given city.
After obtaining the coordinate data, the temperature of that location is displayed.

REQUIREMENTS:
1. Local DB with the following configuration:
    schema:evelb
    user:root
    password:root
    host:localhost
    port:3306
    - If they cannot be met, modify the connection string in the .env file.

2. Install Symfony binary:
    Windows: https://get.symfony.com/cli/setup.exe
    Linux: run 'wget https://get.symfony.com/cli/installer -O - | bash'.

3. Install composer
    Windows: https://getcomposer.org/Composer-Setup.exe
    Linux: run 'apt install composer'.

4. Install PHP7

5. Download the code from GitHub:
    https://github.com/jlorenzo681/prueba_evelb.git

EXECUTION:
Open a console in the project directory (test_evelb) 2.
2. Run 'composer install'.
3. Execute 'php bin/console doctrine:migrations:migrate' 4.
4. Run 'symfony server:start'.
5. Open http://localhost:8000 in the browser
